social_posts.post_text:
Something FUN coming SOON for @tsgashville Volume 6 🤍

Big thank you’s to @meaganharris, @anastasiiaphotography & @brianadariy_ for bringing the vision to life.

Next month marks 3 years since the dream of @uncommonsocialco came to life.

Three years have given me the beautiful gift of experience. Along the way, I’m SO grateful to have forged wonderful connections with fellow dreamers and doers to collaborate on remarkable projects that pushed our boundaries beyond what was expected! The lessons learned from successes (and even failures) stretched me in ways both known and unknown—all while allowing moments of reflection to drive greater growth ahead.

Every day I am reminded how lucky I am to be able to do something that means so much me. My heart is IN it. Even when the most glamorous thing on the agenda is blog posts and eblasts till 1am, it's all worth it in the end because of how @uncommonsocialco has impacted me and those around me - connecting heartstrings far beyond anything I ever imagined!

So cheers to 3 YEARS, and cheers to many, many more.
Charleston weekend recap 🫶🏻 My happy place!!

Have you checked out Asheville’s hottest new hotel, @therestorationasheville? Come with me to tour this stunning property located 🤍 in downtown avl.

But first, let’s talk food! @theexchangeasheville serves up an amazing brunch with dishes like Vanilla Bean French Toast and Braised Duck Hash. Add this to your brunch bucket-list!

After brunch, we made our way to visit the Draftsmans Bar downstairs. It’s complete with an arcade and bowling alley opening on June 20th - epic. And to cap off your visit, head up to @theobservatoryasheville for the perfect instagram pics & breathtaking rooftop views.

Scout is OUT! We had an unforgettable night at the launch event of @tsgasheville Volume 6, hosted at the stunning @momentumgallery.

It was a true celebration of our vibrant small business community, filled with talented movers and makers who are the heart and soul of Asheville.

A special and heartfelt shoutout goes to @meaganharris of @tsgasheville for giving @uncommonsocialco with the invaluable opportunity to be part of this important mission.

Being able to contribute, even in a small way, to fostering a sense of community and showcasing the extraordinary talents that define our city is a privilege that will always be so close to my 🤍! 

📸 @amber_hatley
Seeing spots & seeing lots. Instagram, meet little miss Ella 🤍

I started Uncommon Social Co. right before what felt like the end of the world. March 2020.👀

Leaving my marketing 9-5 and dropping out of school after just one semester, was a wild leap of faith.

As I saw the world changing and, noticed things shifting in my own local community, it was clear that people needed support. 

My little community, like so many other small cities was struggling in the digital realm during the virtual shift.

With everyone operating virtually, local businesses found themselves adrift, unsure of how to stay connected, what to share on social, and how to promote their products and services.

SO many uncertainties.

What seemed like the WORST time to start a new business venture turned into a beautiful and unique opportunity to contribute to my local community, helping them stay connected.

With all this in mind, the core essence of Uncommon has always revolved around community and connection.

Presently, nearly half of our clients hail from Asheville, NC (my sweet lil mountain hometown), and it holds a special place in my heart to continue supporting these businesses as they thrive and grow.

It's this tight-knit local community, so dear to my heart, that breathed life into Uncommon Social Co., and for that, I am so grateful. 🫶🏻 you AVL! 

📸 @yahzay @_jadair
